<h3>Harness the Carbonation Calculating Power of the Internet</h3>
<p>Once you=E2=80=99ve established your target carbonation level, you=E2=80=
=99ll need to calculate the amount of priming sugar needed to produce the d=
esired carbonation.</p>
<p>Homebrewing is as much an art as it is a science, so if you=E2=80=99d ra=
ther not spend your days running numbers on a chalkboard like an =E2=80=998=
0s movie professor, you can get fast and accurate answers using a priming s=
ugar calculator, which will happily <a href=3D"https://www.hopsteiner.com/c=
o2-calculator/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" data-lasso-id=3D"251663"=
>do the math for you</a>.</p>
<h3>Carbonation Tablets Take the Pain Out of Priming Your Homebrew</h3>
<p>In a real hurry? You can simplify the process of <a href=3D"https://www.=
brewcabin.com/bottling-beer/" rel=3D"noopener" data-lasso-id=3D"251664">bot=
tling beer</a> by using <a href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01CAC8HHI?tag=
=3Dbrewcabin-20" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow noopener" data-lasso-id=
=3D"251665" data-lasso-name=3D"Coopers Priming Sugar Tablets">priming sugar=
 tablets</a>. You=E2=80=99ll get your beer bubbling in no time without havi=
ng to become the kid from <em>Good Will Hunting</em>.</p>
<p>Added directly to the bottles at bottling time, priming tablets make it =
as easy to prime one bottle as it is a dozen. You can usually find them in =
two varieties: straight priming sugar tablets, often called <em>carbonation=
 drops</em>, and <em>conditioning tablets</em>, which contain DME and headi=
ng powder (a blend of dextrose and gum arabic designed to promote head rete=
ntion) as well as corn sugar.</p>
<p>Both are extremely easy to use=E2=80=94just follow the directions on the=
 package.</p>
