noopener" data-lasso-id=3D"251669" data-lasso-name=3D"Domino Pure Cane Gran=
ulated White Sugar">table sugar</a></li>
<li>1 =C2=BC cups (181 grams) of <a href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0038=
O5N4I?tag=3Dbrewcabin-20" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow noopener" data-=
lasso-id=3D"251670" data-lasso-name=3D"Briess Light Dry Malt Extract">light=
 dry malt extract (DME)</a></li>
<li>=C2=BD to 1 cup of <a href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01IR6J4CI?tag=
=3Dbrewcabin-20" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow noopener" data-lasso-id=
=3D"251671" data-lasso-name=3D"Nature Nate's 100% Pure Raw &amp; Unfiltered=
 Organic Honey">honey</a>, which can vary in composition (see below)</li>
</ul>
<p>These measurements account for the differences in volume and fermentabil=
ity for each substance, and serve as a reminder that it=E2=80=99s usually b=
est to weigh your ingredients to achieve the best results. But you can fine=
-tune that with the formulas to make sure you hit your target carbonation a=
nd brew the best beer possible.</p>
<p>For each formula, we=E2=80=99ve provided an example solution based on th=
